# LAPERLE - GROUP NORMS AND COLLABORATIVE


### Purpose

Our goal is to foster a collaborative space where every participant feels respected, informed, and motivated to engage. We aim to build a culture of shared ownership and mutual support.

###  Meeting Protocol

Agenda Preparation: The Facilitator drafts and distributes the agenda at least one day before the meeting.

Timeliness: Sessions begin and conclude as scheduled, with consideration for all time zones.
Readiness: Participants are expected to review the agenda and any relevant materials beforehand.
Note-Taking: The Scribe captures key points and action items, which are shared within 24 hours.
Topic Discipline: Discussions remain focused; unrelated items are logged for future follow-up.

### Schedule & Deliverables

**Planned Meetings:**
 Every Thursday : Review draft and assign tasks.
 Every Saturday: Finalize deliverables and resolve pending issues.
 Recording Lead: Louis Kervens will manage meeting recordings.
 Scheduling Tool: 
 Participation Goal: Actively participate in every session

### Communication Channels

 Main Platform:  WhatsApp (primary), Google Meet (Group meeting and workplace)

 Video & Archives: Google Meet for live sessions; recordings will be shared.


### Decision-Making

 Voting Process: Decisions are made by majority vote; the Facilitator resolves any ties.
 Weighted Input: For complex topics, weighted voting will be used to reflect diverse perspectives.
 Equity: Alternate sessions will be scheduled to accommodate those who miss meetings.

### Roles & Responsibilities

 **Coordinator:** Designs the agenda, leads the meeting
 and maintains structure.
**Secretary:** Documents discussions, tracks follow-ups,
  and shares meeting notes.
 **Meeting Monitor:** Keeps the meeting on schedule, 
  signals transitions, and promotes time efficiency.
 **Reference:** [Agenda Draft – Sample Role Guide]

### Respect & Empathy

 Acknowledge and respect, time commitments, and working styles.
 Offer feedback that is constructive and focused on ideas, 
not individuals.
 Encourage balanced participation by practicing “step up, step back.”

### Accountability & Trust

 Follow through on assigned tasks within agreed timelines.
 Reach out early if support or clarification is needed.
 Address concerns openly and work together to find fair solutions.

### Continuous Improvement

 Host monthly reflection sessions using the “What worked / 
What could improve” format.
 Adjust team norms and workflows based on feedback and evolving needs.

 Note: This document is dynamic and will evolve as our team grows and adapts.
